        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="lecture-1-introduction">Lecture 1 Introduction</h1>
<!-- more -->
<h2 id="why-networks">Why Networks?</h2>
<h3 id="many-types-of-data-are-networks-and-graphs">Many Types of Data are Networks and Graphs</h3>
<p><strong>Networks</strong>: A general language for describing complex systems of interating entities.（描述复杂系统中的关联实体）<br>
Two types of Networks/Graphs:</p>
<ol>
<li>Networks (Natural Graph): Society, Communication systems, Interaction between genes/proteins</li>
<li>Information Graphs: Information, Knowledge, Similarity networks<br>
<img src="https://zhangyumeng1sjtu.github.io/post-images/fig1-1.png" alt="" width="700" height="300" loading="lazy"><br>
<img src="https://zhangyumeng1sjtu.github.io/post-images/fig1-2.png" alt="" width="700" height="300" loading="lazy"></li>
</ol>
<h3 id="networks-and-applications">Networks and Applications</h3>
<p>Questions: 网络系统是怎样组织的，如何描述网络的属性，如何利用网络的关联结构等<br>
Ways to analyze networks:</p>
<ol>
<li>对结点的属性进行预测（Node classification）</li>
<li>预测两个结点之间是否存在连接边（Link prediction）</li>
<li>识别紧密联系的结点簇（Community detection）</li>
<li>衡量结点或者网络之间的相似性（Network similarity）<br>
Network applications (exmaples):<br>
<img src="https://zhangyumeng1sjtu.github.io/post-images/fig1-3.png" alt="" width="800" height="300" loading="lazy"></li>
</ol>
<h2 id="sturcture-of-graphs">Sturcture of Graphs</h2>
<p><strong>Definition</strong>: A network is a collection of objects where some pairs of objects are connected by links<br>
<strong>Components</strong>:<br>
Object: nodes (结点), vertices (顶点)，用<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">V</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.22222em;">V</span></span></span></span>表示<br>
Interactions: links, edges (边)，用<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.05764em;">E</span></span></span></span>表示<br>
System: network, graph，用<span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>V</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">G(V,E)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault">G</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.22222em;">V</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;"></span><span class="mord mathdefault" style="margin-right:0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>表示</p>
<h3 id="choice-of-network-representation">Choice of Network Representation</h3>
<p>有向图和无向图<br>
